cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper deals with object detection, specifically in the context of vehicle detection. The use of visual and geometrical clusters to handle intra-category diversity suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The use of an AdaBoost detection scheme and pixel lookup features suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The analysis of detection performance and orientation estimation accuracy suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and computer security (cs.CR), as accurate detection and orientation estimation are important for autonomous vehicles and security systems.
